an ancient Germanic name, composed of the elements <i>bic</i> ‘sharp point, pointed weapon’ + <i>hard</i> ‘hardy, brave, strong’."]}]},{"name":"Nicholas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the post-classical Greek personal name <i>Nikolaos</i>, derived from <i>nikē</i> ‘victory’ + <i>laos</i> ‘people’. The spelling with <i>-ch-</i> first occurred as early as the 12th century, and became firmly established at the time of the Reformation, although  <b>Nicolas</b>  is still occasionally found.  St Nicholas  was a 4th-century bishop of Myra in Lycia, about whom virtually nothing factual is known, although a vast body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705182,"age":30,"year":"1066","julianDay":2110409,"title":"Battle of Hastings","description":"Battle of Hastings was fought between the Norman-French army and the battle-wary English army on October 14, 1066. Duke William of Normandy believed he was the rightful king rather than Harold, who had been crowned king several months earlier. Harold was killed in battle and William was crowned king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705183,"age":50,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705184,"age":60,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Nicholas de Picard was born in 1036, in Skipton, Yorkshire, England. She had at least 1 son with Nicholas de Picard. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1036–":"1036–Surnud","1030–Male":"1030–Surnud","1066–1160":"1066–1160","1036–Female":"1036–Surnud","1036":"1036","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1030":"1030","1160":"1160","Skipton, Yorkshire, England":"Skipton, Yorkshire, England","Skipton-in-Craven, Yorkshire, England":"Skipton, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1036–":"1036–Kuollut","1030–Male":"1030–Kuollut","1066–1160":"1066–1160","1036–Female":"1036–Kuollut","1036":"1036","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1030":"1030","1160":"1160","Skipton, Yorkshire, England":"Skipton, Yorkshire, England","Skipton-in-Craven, Yorkshire, England":"Skipton, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1036–":"1036–Décédée","1030–Male":"1030–Décédé","1066–1160":"1066–1160","1036–Female":"1036–Décédée","1036":"1036","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1030":"1030","1160":"1160","Skipton, Yorkshire, England":"Skipton, Everwyck, Angleterre","Skipton-in-Craven, Yorkshire, England":"Skipton, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Nicholas de Picard est née en 1036, à Skipton, Everwyck, Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Nicholas de Picar